---
import HomeLayout from "../layouts/HomeLayout.astro";
import "../styles/content.css";
---

<HomeLayout
  title="About — 1Quest"
  description="Why we built 1Quest and how patient AI teaching fits school, JEE, NEET, and UPSC prep."
>
  <article class="inner">
    <header class="inner__header wrap-read">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="inner__title">Built for learners who want to <em>understand</em></h1>
      <p class="inner__lead">
        We build tools for students and parents who care about the method — not just finishing a
        syllabus checkbox or getting a finished answer from a chatbot.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="wrap-read inner__body prose-lg">
      <h2>What this site is</h2>
      <p>
        This is the public home of <strong>1Quest</strong>: guides, explainers, and topic hubs that
        help you discover what to study and why it matters. The interactive tutor, weekly plans,
        and full product live in the 1Quest app.
      </p>

      <h2>What we believe</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Good explanations beat long lists of facts.</li>
        <li>Structure reduces anxiety when the syllabus is huge.</li>
        <li>Patience is a feature — especially when a child says “I still don't get it.”</li>
        <li>Technology should adapt to how you actually study, not the other way around.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who we serve</h2>
      <p>
        Today we focus on <strong>school students</strong> and <strong>UPSC aspirants</strong>.
        <strong>JEE</strong> and <strong>NEET</strong> are on the way — same philosophy, built for
        those exams when they're ready.
      </p>

      <h2>What's next</h2>
      <p>
        We'll add more lesson pages, blog posts, and syllabus-aligned hubs here over time. For now
        this is a clean foundation — fast pages, clear navigation, and room to grow.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</HomeLayout>
